{"name":"The Wishing Well's Price","type":"item","img":"icons/magic/water/barrier-ice-crystal-wall-jagged-blue.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","description":"You have learned the truth about Smaragd's Wishing Well: it grants wishes, but corrupts them in cruel ways. The villagers prove this—one wished for wealth and became living gold statue, another for eternal beauty and became porcelain doll, another to never sleep and went mad from exhaustion. You can make ONE wish at the well, but you understand the price. Before wishing, make a Check vs OL Hard (7): on success, phrase your wish carefully enough that corruption is minimized (GM interprets fairly but still with consequence). On failure, wish is granted in most twisted way possible. Alternatively, use your knowledge to resist the well's temptation: once per Scene, when an NPC or enemy tries to use the well, you can intervene and explain the cost—make Social Check to convince them. This represents wisdom to see through false promises.","tags":["knowledge","temptation","wishes","wisdom"],"requirements":"Investigate the Villagers of Emerald and learn their wish-corruption stories, OR witness Henkle or enemy using the well","somaCost":0,"limitations":"You can only make ONE wish per campaign—choose wisely. If you wish for something selfless (helping others, stopping Henkle, saving companions), GM should minimize corruption. Selfish wishes corrupt more severely. The well cannot grant impossible wishes (resurrection, time travel without Compass Rose, true love). Some villagers may become hostile if you try to destroy their 'gift' even if it's a curse."},"_id":"2d35cc08429c8fb8"}
{"name":"Fragment of the Red Compass","type":"item","img":"icons/sundries/misc/compass-brass-red-orange.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","description":"You possess the southern (red) piece of the Compass Rose that Helga guarded. This bloodstone needle pulses like a heartbeat and points toward the nearest Compass Rose piece (now north toward the emerald center piece in Smaragd). While carrying this fragment, you sense the life force of creatures within 30 feet—useful for detecting hidden enemies or determining if someone is dying. Once per Scene, activate the fragment to track one specific person you've met: the needle points toward them for one Scene, even through walls. Warning: this piece is stained with centuries of blood magic—carrying it may attract blood-hungry creatures or cause disturbing visions of Helga's victims.","tags":["temporal","navigation","life-sense","artifact"],"requirements":"Obtained from Helga (through combat, negotiation, or inheriting after her death)","somaCost":0,"limitations":"Life-sense is passive but overwhelming in crowded areas. Tracking requires you to have previously met the target. Each additional Compass Rose piece you carry increases the burden—GM may call for Fortitude Checks to resist temporal displacement headaches. Henkle desperately wants this piece."},"_id":"51f57aa2ea35ebaa"}
{"name":"Traveler from Tomorrow","type":"item","img":"icons/magic/time/clock-stopwatch-white-gray.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","description":"Through encounters with OZena, Lowe, Hirnloser, and Dose, you've learned they're from the future (early 1900s America). You can recognize anachronistic references: when Hirnloser mentions 'electricity' or Dose talks about 'hospitals,' you understand these are things that don't exist yet in 1780. Once per Scene, leverage your knowledge of their future origin: gain +1 to Social Checks when convincing them you know their secret, recognize which of OZena's behaviors are desperate cries for help versus true malice, identify objects or knowledge that came from their era. This gift represents empathy—understanding they're displaced and suffering, not inherently evil.","tags":["knowledge","social","empathy","time-travel"],"requirements":"Have meaningful conversation with at least one time-displaced character, piece together clues about their origin","somaCost":0,"limitations":"This knowledge doesn't grant future technology or science. You understand they're from the future but can't replicate their world. Henkle will become hostile if he realizes you know too much."},"_id":"8ac8d5f2015f3595"}
{"name":"Manycorpses' Tragedy","type":"item","img":"icons/magic/death/skull-horned-worn-white.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","description":"You witnessed or learned the tragic story of Manycorpses—two lovers fused by Helga's blood magic into a monstrous form, forced to serve the witch who destroyed them. This knowledge has hardened your resolve against blood magic's corruption and taught you about the power of love even in monstrous forms. Once per scenario, when facing a creature or person transformed by dark magic, you can attempt to reach their humanity: make a Social Check opposed by their Opposition Level. On success, they hesitate for one Exchange (losing their action), or if they were once good, they may actively help you for one Scene before the magic reasserts control. This represents your ability to see the person beneath the monster.","tags":["social","empathy","anti-corruption","monster-humanization"],"requirements":"Witness Manycorpses' tragedy, learn their story from servants, OR speak with them and recognize their suffering","somaCost":0,"limitations":"Only works on beings who were once fully human/humane and transformed against their will. Does not work on creatures who chose corruption or were always monstrous. The transformed being suffers greatly when fighting their compulsion—using this gift is merciful but painful for them."},"_id":"ab3417f82602b28c"}
{"name":"Infusion of Purity","type":"item","img":"icons/consumables/potions/potion-bottle-corked-labeled-green.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","description":"You have learned Wolfgang's secret recipe to break blood magic: **Infusion of Purity** requires burdock root (courage), nettle (protection), hyssop (purification), and **elderberry** (life). When you spend 1 Increment preparing and consuming this infusion, you gain immunity to blood magic for one Scene: Helga cannot control your blood, puppet you if wounded, or drain your life force. Additionally, if Helga is wounded while you have active Infusion in your system and your blood touches her, it acts as poison—negating her Blood Witch regeneration and causing her to age rapidly. This infusion represents nature's power to cleanse corruption. Wolfgang grows these herbs in his secret greenhouse—you must either rescue him or find his hidden garden.","tags":["consumable","protection","anti-magic","crafting"],"requirements":"Rescue Wolfgang from blood servitude and learn his recipe, OR discover his hidden greenhouse and decipher his botanical notes","somaCost":0,"limitations":"Requires 1 Increment to prepare and consume. Ingredients must be fresh—dried herbs lose potency. Only works against blood magic, not other supernatural threats. Effect lasts one Scene (30-60 minutes). Elderberry is the rare component—Wolfgang may have limited supply."},"_id":"b54246d4db2bd62f"}
{"name":"Sanctuary of Gelb","type":"item","img":"icons/environment/settlement/house-small.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","description":"You have earned the trust and gratitude of the outcasts in the village of Gelb. The villagers—people with leontiasis, elephantiasis, severe burns, missing limbs—see you as protector rather than threat. While in Gelb, you have sanctuary: free lodging, meals, basic medical care. Villagers warn you of dangers, share rumors about Rot and Smaragd, offer their unique skills. Once per scenario, call upon a villager's specialized knowledge (herbalism, tracking, local history). If Margareta survived, she provides magical insight. If she died protecting them, they honor you as her successor and will risk their lives to help you stop Henkle.","tags":["social","sanctuary","allies","knowledge"],"requirements":"Save Klaus from kidnappers, show compassion to outcasts, or defeat those threatening Gelb","somaCost":0,"limitations":"Villagers are not warriors—they provide support, not combat aid. If you betray their trust or harm them, lose this gift permanently. Henkle or OZena may target Gelb to hurt you."},"_id":"c63d3a28a32064ca"}
{"name":"Time Thief","type":"item","img":"icons/magic/time/hourglass-tilted-gray.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","description":"You have learned Henkle's secret: his Hot-Air Balloon is powered by Time Tokens harvested from temporal anomalies caused by the Compass Rose's presence in 1780. You can disrupt his escape plan by stealing or destroying his Time Tokens. Once per Scene, when Henkle would gain a Time Token (combat start, delaying him, Hunters lost in Illusory Labyrinth), make a Check vs his OL (5): on success, you intercept the temporal energy—Henkle gains no Token, and you gain insight into time flow (ask GM one yes/no question about immediate future: 'Will the balloon launch this Scene?' 'Is reinforcement arriving?'). If you accumulate 3 Time Tokens before Henkle does, you can either: sabotage his balloon permanently (it will never fly), or redirect the time portal to send companions home instead of Henkle escaping.","tags":["sabotage","temporal","tactical","counter-villain"],"requirements":"Discover Henkle's Time Token mechanic through investigation, eavesdropping, or studying the Hot-Air Balloon","somaCost":0,"limitations":"Henkle notices when Tokens are stolen—he becomes hostile and focuses on eliminating you. Each stolen Token causes temporal headache (GM may impose -1 to Mental Checks while carrying multiple Tokens). If you die while carrying Tokens, they dissipate harmlessly but Henkle can collect new ones. Redirecting time portal requires having both Tokens AND at least two Compass Rose pieces."},"_id":"cba0ed886c26aae6"}
{"name":"Companion's Transformation","type":"item","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-orange.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","description":"You have befriended one of OZena's three companions (Lowe, Hirnloser, or Dose) and witnessed their character arc complete: the coward finding courage, the 'brainless' proving genius, or the hollow finding heart through love. Their transformation inspires you. Choose one companion you've built relationship with. Once per scenario, channel their realized virtue: **Lowe's Courage** (reroll any Fear/Intimidation Check, taking better result), **Hirnloser's Genius** (ask GM one specific tactical question—'What's the hidden weakness?' 'What would genius do?'—and receive honest answer), or **Dose's Love** (when protecting someone you care for, +2 to Defense or one automatic success on Protect action). This gift represents how witnessing others' growth helps us find our own strength.","tags":["inspiration","character-development","virtue","social"],"requirements":"Build meaningful relationship with at least one companion across multiple Parts, witness or facilitate their Part Three transformation","somaCost":0,"limitations":"Can only channel virtue of companion you've actually befriended—can't choose all three. If that companion dies or betrays you before their arc completes, lose this gift. Using this gift in their presence grants them +1 to their next Check (your faith empowers them)."},"_id":"ebaab1be98d6a7c0"}
{"name":"Fragment of the Yellow Compass","type":"item","img":"icons/sundries/misc/compass-brass-blue-brown.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","description":"You possess the western (yellow) piece of the Compass Rose that Margareta guarded. This golden needle hums with temporal energy and points toward the nearest Compass Rose piece (currently southeast toward Helga's red piece in Rot). While carrying this fragment, you experience temporal echoes: glimpses of past and future in this location. Once per Scene, consult the fragment to receive a vision—GM reveals one useful fact about the immediate past or near future. Warning: carrying Compass Rose pieces makes you a target for those seeking to control time itself.","tags":["temporal","navigation","visions","artifact"],"requirements":"Obtained from Margareta (through persuasion, combat, or inheriting after her death)","somaCost":0,"limitations":"Visions are fragmentary and open to interpretation. Fragment grows heavier as you collect more pieces (physical burden of temporal power). Henkle can sense when pieces are brought together."},"_id":"fbc853026dd34b47"}
